            "body": ">  we need to set vim.o.eventignore and restore it after calling this func.\n\n`eventignorewin` is local to window. \n\n> using noautocmd does not shown error when call nvim_win_set_config.\n\nmaybe just throw error when value changed \n\n```diff\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/api/win_config.c b/src/nvim/api/win_config.c\nindex 7ca6121d01..4b256afed0 100644\n--- a/src/nvim/api/win_config.c\n+++ b/src/nvim/api/win_config.c\n@@ -1380,7 +1380,7 @@ static bool parse_win_config(win_T *wp, Dict(win_config) *config, WinConfig *fco\n   }\n\n   if (HAS_KEY_X(config, noautocmd)) {\n-    if (wp) {\n+    if (wp && config->noautocmd != fconfig->noautocmd) {\n       api_set_error(err, kErrorTypeValidation, \"'noautocmd' cannot be used with existing windows\");\n       goto fail;\n     }\n```",
